annotation.TEXT: I think I'm relatively safe from the cheepos near the bottom center of the screen, just like in later Mario games. But, I think the cheepos are a bit less predictable here, so I can't guarantee that I'm completely safe.
Yep, I can go through. And, I bet the reason is because there's an invisible block right next to the wall.
Whoa. That was a Podoboo that I just star-killed. However, it will eventually come back, so be careful.

Hello, and welcome back to New Strange Mario Bros.! Alright, I've gone back in time to replay 2-2 in full, and SuperSupermario24 suggested that I hold left and mash A to dodge that first fish, so let's see how that works out...
Oh, I know this place. Well, this is good, because I can start restocking on lives after what just happened.
Unfortunately, you can't fire fireballs while "duck swimming" like this, so just land on something and then start swimming again without ducking if you want to shoot stuff.
Those gray koopas are actually green koopas, so they'll walk right off the ledge.
Whoops, lost a flower that I don't need. Wow, this hack gives the player a lot of 1-ups.
And, we're back! Now, let's play 3-1!
PIranha plant used Bite! Critical hit! Mario fainted!
Mwahahaha!!! That reminds me a bit of world 0-3.
Not stopping for flowers or multi-coin blocks. I've got Hammer Bros. to slay!
Whoa, nearly got nibbled by the same piranha plant again. Yeah, this looks like the place where the bonus room dumps me.
Nuts. Only 1000. If you kick a koopa or buzzy shell I think on the very last frame before it wakes up, you can get 8000 points.
Demo count: 6
...Well, that just happened. And I was holding right, too. I hate how sometimes this game won't let a 2-tile high plumber into a 3-tile high opening as he's falling. That just seems wrong.
Yeah, so if there's a hidden block adjacent to something solid to its right, you can pass through that solid object from the left if the hidden block hasn't been revealed.
Alright, after the fireworks are done, I'm going to travel back to the present time where I've paused while invisible at the start of 3-1.
And, this goal screen looks familiar, so I guess I'm done.
Here again? I was hoping for whatever this hack replaced 3-1's sky bonus area with...
Alright, I'm skipping this bonus room this time.
...Heh, heh, heh. Man, this is getting silly.
I mainly just want my lost lives back.
Demo count: 3
Also, I wonder why the first red koopa here was falling down the stairs? It's not like it was a red parakoopa that I removed the wings of...
Man, that would've been so cool if my fireball hit the parakoopa there. Oh, well.
Sigh... Let's try this again...
5-death combo!

Nuts. I thought I'd be timed perfectly for the fireworks, but I actually hit the flag too soon. Oh, well. At least I was so fast I got the music glitch to occur. (Happens if you grab a flagpole with enough star power left.)
4-death combo!
Yes! And now 3-1 is completely done! That only took a half dozen deaths.
Demo count: 8
And, actually, there's a second hidden block down below. These are probably there just in case you broke all of the bricks to the left and scrolled the pipe off the screen, so you won't be trapped.
Now, let's see... If I jump at the wall just right here...
Ha! By holding A as I exit, I can... get nibbled on by the piranha plant. But, at least I avoided dying. Also, this pipe takes me... right back to the same bonus room. Swell.
What does "TILOU!" mean?
Whoa, what's with all the falling goombas?
Demo count: 7
Now, let's not go down this pipe this time...

Oh, yeah. I don't know if I've ever explained this trick before, but if you start swimming while you're ducking, you'll still technically be ducking while you're swimming, even if it doesn't look like it. So, your head is no longer part of your hitbox. This only applies if you're big, of course.
Oh, good. I think the flying cheepos stopped. Also, the blocks are spelling something...
Oh, geez. This setup? Well, I guess this is the end of world 3-1. But, it's not like I'm hurting for lives anyway.
I'm lucky I didn't crash into a cheepo upon coming back down. Also, I could've certainly used the springboard to get on the roof there, but I wanted to stay down here, as usual.
Demo count: 4
And, despite all those deaths, and me not getting the 1-up trick on the ending stairs working, I'm up to "Crown-E" lives, which is 24.
Man, doing that has gotta be giving Mario a headache.
...Oookay... I have no excuse for that one.
Brutal combo! (6 hits)
Alright, foodge it. I was having trouble getting the 1-up trick to work for some reason, and I don't want to waste too much time here.
Oooh, my god... Okay, Some Guy, get ahold of yourself here... Just don't screw up 16 more times in a row, and you'll be fine.
Mario used IDCLIP! It's super effective!

Yeah, using a springboard in a water level is similar to using a green springboard in The Lost Levels. However, I can't control myself while I'm off screen in a water level, and the timer stops while I'm very far off screen for some reason.
Whew! I saved that guy from drowning himself.
Toasty!
Huzzah! It worked! ...Whoa!!! Okay, let's try to find a relatively safe spot from these fishies... Oh, and now, instead of going down that first pipe, I'll just keep going to the right.
Demo count: 5
Geez, why am I dying so much in 3-1 here? Somehow, I blame Google.
Okay... Something just caused me to glitch into the wall right there, and I think I know what it was. I'll talk about this later.
Oh, check this out. BOING!!!
Wait, is this...? Yes, this is indeed that star run level that I've already played back in world 0! (It was 0-3.) This ought to be quick and fun.
Brutal combo! (6 deaths)
Oh, and I do know how to avoid dying when exiting the bonus room there. It's just that I was unprepared that time.
Now first, let's get my life back, and then investigate that wall I ran through last time.
Ooh, coins and ? blocks. Unfortunately, trying to hit blocks while underwater in SMB just results in you bouncing off of them with no effect. I wonder why that is...
No, wait. Stop! You'll fall in the water!
King combo! (11 hits)
Whoa, lots of parakoopas, and one of them got stuck in the blocks. I'll save you!
For right now, I'm going to play through the rest of this room.
What the heck?!
GAAAMMMEEE!!!
GAAAMMMEEE!!!
Alright, I think that's enough for today, so next time, I'll be starting off with 3-3! To be continued... Ooh, coins!
Space-time rewind count: 3
And there we go. Four 1-up mushrooms makes up for those 4 deaths.
And after all that, there wasn't even anything in those bricks!
